Sure! Below is a simple web app that allows users to collect colored crystals. The app features a basic layout with embedded CSS for styling and JavaScript for functionality. You can copy and paste the entire code block into an HTML file and open it in a web browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Collect the Colored Crystals</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f0f8ff;
            text-align: center;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #4a90e2;
        }
        #crystal-container {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        .crystal {
            width: 50px;
            height: 50px;
            margin: 10px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: transform 0.2s;
        }
        .crystal:hover {
            transform: scale(1.1);
        }
        #score {
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-size: 24px;
            color: #333;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Collect the Colored Crystals!</h1>
    <div id="crystal-container"></div>
    <div id="score">Score: 0</div>

    <script>
        const colors = ['#FF5733', '#33FF57', '#3357FF', '#F1C40F', '#8E44AD', '#E67E22'];
        let score = 0;

        function createCrystals() {
            const container = document.getElementById('crystal-container');
            for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
                const crystal = document.createElement('div');
                crystal.className = 'crystal';
                crystal.style.backgroundColor = colors[Math.floor(Math.random() * colors.length)];
                crystal.addEventListener('click', () => collectCrystal(crystal));
                container.appendChild(crystal);
            }
        }

        function collectCrystal(crystal) {
            score++;
            document.getElementById('score').innerText = `Score: ${score}`;
            crystal.style.display = 'none'; // Hide the collected crystal
        }

        // Initialize the game
        createCrystals();
    </script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use:
1. Copy the code above.
2. Open a text editor (like Notepad, VSCode, or any HTML editor).
3. Paste the code into a new file.
4. Save the file with a `.html` extension (e.g., `collect_crystals.html`).
5. Open the saved file in a web browser.

### Features:
- The app displays a grid of colored crystals.
- Clicking on a crystal increases the score and hides the crystal.
- The score is displayed at the bottom of the page. 

Feel free to modify the colors, number of crystals, or any other aspect to customize the app further!
